---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Writing - Rabiah Khanum">
  <div class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-50 via-white to-purple-50">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
      <div class="text-center mb-16">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6" style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;">
          Writing
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Reflections on books, creativity, and the art of thoughtful reading
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- LinkedIn Article Card -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden border border-slate-100">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-500 to-blue-600 h-2"></div>
          <div class="p-8 md:p-12">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-teal-600" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path d="M19 0h-14c-2.761 0-5 2.239-5 5v14c0 2.761 2.239 5 5 5h14c2.762 0 5-2.239 5-5v-14c0-2.761-2.238-5-5-5zm-11 19h-3v-11h3v11zm-1.5-12.268c-.966 0-1.75-.79-1.75-1.764s.784-1.764 1.75-1.764 1.75.79 1.75 1.764-.783 1.764-1.75 1.764zm13.5 12.268h-3v-5.604c0-3.368-4-3.113-4 0v5.604h-3v-11h3v1.765c1.396-2.586 7-2.777 7 2.476v6.759z"/>
              </svg>
              <span class="text-sm font-medium text-teal-600 uppercase tracking-wider">LinkedIn Article</span>
            </div>
            
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6" style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;">
              Why We Can't Stop Ignoring Books
            </h2>
            
            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-700 mb-8">
              <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
                I stumbled upon Niall Ferguson's piece "Without Books We Will Be Barbarians" through an Instagram reel, ironically enough, and by some miracle, actually read it instead of feeding it into ChatGPT for a summary. His reflections on Bradbury's <em>Fahrenheit 451</em> and Orwell's <em>1984</em> struck a chord, and I couldn't help but share my own thoughts.
              </p>
              
              <p class="leading-relaxed mb-4">
                Ferguson argues that we're voluntarily turning away from literacy, not through totalitarian force, but through the allure of consumer society. The moment smartphones and flashy technology became accessible, we collectively developed an aversion to deep reading. Why dive into pages-long manuscripts that require critical thinking when ready-made answers are just one click or one prompt away?
              </p>

              <p class="leading-relaxed">
                But here's the thing: what I've read has shaped me in ways that no series, movie, or podcast ever has. Reading and making sense of text independently embeds ideas more firmly in the mind than most other modes of consuming information. And I, for one, would feel a deep sense of loss if I ever stopped reading.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-50 to-blue-50 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
              <p class="text-slate-700 italic leading-relaxed">
                "Books became my best friends. There was something about the stories bound between those covers, and the myriad species of Folk weaving in and out of them, each one a mystery begging to be solved."
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 mt-2">— Emily Wilde's Encyclopaedia of Faeries, Heather Fawcett</p>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-center justify-between pt-6 border-t border-slate-200">
              <div class="text-sm text-slate-500">
                Published on LinkedIn • January 15, 2026 • 5 min read
              </div>
              <a 
                href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/why-we-cant-stop-ignoring-books-rabiah-khanum-y4aqf/?trackingId=rCTd2uQNAjgV4kOlSDmV9A%3D%3D" 
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-500 to-blue-600 text-white rounded-lg font-medium hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105"
              >
                Read Full Article
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
                </svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Creative Writing Card -->
      <div class="mb-12">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden border border-slate-100">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500 to-pink-600 h-2"></div>
          <div class="p-8 md:p-12">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
              <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-purple-600" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15.232 5.232l3.536 3.536m-2.036-5.036a2.5 2.5 0 113.536 3.536L6.5 21.036H3v-3.572L16.732 3.732z" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-sm font-medium text-purple-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Fiction Writing</span>
            </div>
            
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6" style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;">
              Dream a Fiction
            </h2>
            
            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-slate-700 mb-8">
              <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
                A friend was collecting writing samples to understand how different people write, whether fiction or personal stories. I wrote this short story synopsis in a few minutes, letting the words flow without overthinking.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="flex items-center justify-between pt-6 border-t border-slate-200">
              <div class="text-sm text-slate-500">
                Creative Writing Sample • Stream of Consciousness
              </div>
              <a 
                href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}dream-a-fiction`}
                class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-500 to-pink-600 text-white rounded-lg font-medium hover:shadow-lg transition-all duration-300 hover:scale-105"
              >
                Read Full Story
                <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
                </svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Writing Philosophy Section -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-50 to-blue-50 rounded-2xl p-8 md:p-12">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6 text-center" style="font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;">
          On Writing
        </h3>
        <p class="text-lg text-slate-700 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed mb-4">
          Whether I'm documenting complex technical systems or letting fiction pour out in a few minutes, writing has always been about making sense of the world, and leaving something behind that outlasts the moment.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed italic">
          Good writing, technical or creative, makes the complex accessible and the familiar meaningful. And maybe, just maybe, it helps someone else make sense of their own world too.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>